INTERVIEW READY ANSWER (30 Seconds)
=========================================================

A pointer is a variable that stores the address of another variable.
Pointers enable dynamic memory allocation, pass-by-reference semantics,
efficient array traversal, and implementation of complex data structures
like linked lists and trees. Important concepts include null pointers,
dangling pointers, wild pointers, void pointers, pointer arithmetic, and
dynamic memory management using new/delete.

